{"updated_at": "2012-11-29T16:45:10Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-11-29T16:45:10Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/10855781", "id": 10855781, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5872", "issue_id": 5872, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ajsharp/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/ajsharp", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ajsharp/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ajsharp/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ajsharp/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "e4f80e42794094c98a40bfebef4ec292", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ajsharp/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ajsharp", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ajsharp/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/e4f80e42794094c98a40bfebef4ec292?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fd0aae9539e4dd0bd618e5d2598f18707.png", "id": 12774, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ajsharp/events{/privacy}", "login": "ajsharp", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ajsharp/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ajsharp/followers"}, "body": "@rafaelfranca Yea, so, this is happening in a resque job. Adding the following code to re-establish the connection fixed it:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\ntask \"resque:setup\" => :environment do\r\n  Resque.before_fork = Proc.new { ActiveRecord::Base.establish_connection }\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt's not clear to me why this started failing, and why this fixed it, but, that worked!", "_id": {"$oid": "523811e7bd3543c15100d8b4"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5872#issuecomment-10855781"}
